'''Matsugasaki Cave Tomb Cluster''' (松ヶ崎横穴墓群) is a {{ill|cave tomb cluster|ja|横穴墓群遺跡|3=横穴墓|1=Cave tomb|lt=Cave tombs|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/cave tomb cluster|13=User:Immanuelle/Cave tomb|qq=}} dating from the [[:en:Kofun period|Kofun period]] to the early [[:en:Nara period|Nara period]], located in {{ill|Kōnandai, Yokohama|ja|港南台|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kōnandai, Yokohama|qq=}}, [[:en:Kōnan-ku, Yokohama|Kōnan-ku, Yokohama]], [[:en:Yokohama|Yokohama]], [[:en:Kanagawa Prefecture|Kanagawa Prefecture]]. It is part of the {{ill|Itachigawa Basin Rock-Cut Tombs|ja|㹨川流域横穴墓群|ja|㹨川流域横穴墓群|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Itachigawa Basin Rock-Cut Tombs|qq=}} and has been registered as a {{ill|Yokohama City Registered Cultural Property|ja|横浜市登録地域文化財|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yokohama City Registered Cultural Property|qq=}} (Regional Historic Site).<ref>{{Cite web|language=ja|url=https://www.townnews.co.jp/0112/2015/11/26/309854.html|title=港南台 横穴墓群が地域文化財に|website=Town News Kōnan & Sakae Ward Edition|date=2015-11-26|accessdate=2020-07-22}}</ref>
== Overview == The tombs are located on the slope of a hill south of {{ill|Kanagawa Prefectural Yokohama Meihō High School|ja|神奈川県立横浜明朋高等学校|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kanagawa Prefectural Yokohama Meihō High School|qq=}} (formerly {{ill|Kanagawa Prefectural Kōnandai High School|ja|神奈川県立港南台高等学校|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kanagawa Prefectural Kōnandai High School|qq=}}). Administratively, they fall under Kōnan-ku but are situated near the border with [[:en:Sakae-ku, Yokohama|Sakae-ku, Yokohama]], making them closely associated with the Sakae area. The tombs were once counted among the {{ill|Kōnandai Ruins Cluster|ja|港南台遺跡群|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kōnandai Ruins Cluster|qq=}}, and records indicate that eight tombs originally remained.<ref>{{ill|Kanagawa Prefectural Board of Education|ja|神奈川県教育庁社会教育部文化財保護課|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kanagawa Prefectural Board of Education|qq=}}, ''Kōnandai'' (1976), pp. 156-158.</ref> However, the site is now overgrown with trees and underbrush, with only two or three entrances faintly visible.
The tombs feature a distinctive {{ill|Kamakura-style cave tomb|ja|鎌倉型横穴墓|1=Kamakura-style cave tombs|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kamakura-style cave tomb|13=User:Immanuelle/Kamakura-style cave tombs|qq=}} design known as the {{ill|Kajigayatsu-style cave tomb|ja|鍛冶ヶ谷式横穴墓|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kajigayatsu-style cave tomb|qq=}}. This includes a {{ill|burial chamber|ja|玄室|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/burial chamber|qq=}} with a narrow, elongated trapezoidal floor, a semi-cylindrical ceiling, and a small chamber referred to as a "coffin chamber" (棺室) carved into the back wall.<ref>{{ill|Yokohama City Archaeological Research Center|ja|埋蔵文化財センター (横浜市)|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yokohama City Archaeological Research Center|qq=}}, ''Maibun Yokohama 31'' (2015), pp. 1-3.</ref>
On November 13, 2015, the site was designated as a {{ill|Yokohama City Registered Cultural Property|ja|横浜市登録地域文化財|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yokohama City Registered Cultural Property|qq=}}, under the category of "Regional Historic Sites."<ref name=yokohama>{{Cite web|language=ja|title=指定・登録文化財目録|publisher={{ill|Yokohama City Board of Education|ja|横浜市教育委員会|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yokohama City Board of Education|qq=}}|url=https://www.city.yokohama.lg.jp/kurashi/kyodo-manabi/bunkazai/bunya12000.files/0007_20191120.pdf|date=2020-05-29|accessdate=2020-07-24}}</ref>
